# Pod IPs & Pod CIDRs

Two ranges, separate from your VPC/LAN.

- **Pod CIDR** — `192.168.0.0/16` (Calico), `10.244.0.0/16` (Flannel).
- **Service CIDR** — `10.96.0.0/12` (notebook 04).

## Subdivided per node

```
pod CIDR 192.168.0.0/16
 ├ node-1 → 192.168.1.0/24 → pods .5 .6 .7
 └ node-2 → 192.168.2.0/24 → pods .4 .5
```

> `kubectl get node <n> -o jsonpath='{.spec.podCIDR}'`

> **Route by node:** packet for `192.168.2.0/24` → node-2. The **CNI publishes** these routes (BGP / overlay).

## The gotcha

> `192.168.0.0/16` overlaps corp LANs / home routers. Same range as your VPN → **ambiguous.** Prod picks non-overlapping.
